{"word":"G1459 - ἐγκαταλείπω - enkataleípō - eng-kat-al-i'-po - Forsake","slug":"G1459","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐγκαταλείπω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>enkataleípō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>eng-kat-al-i'-po"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Forsake"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x0313;&#x03B3;&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x03C4;&#x03B1;&#x03BB;&#x03B5;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C0;&#x03C9; - egkataleipo&#x0304;</b> - <i>eng-kat-al-i'-po</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G1722\">G1722</a> and <a href=\"#/G2641\">G2641</a>; to <i>leave behind in</i> some place, that is, (in a good sense) <i>let remain over</i>, or (in a bad one) to <i>desert:</i> - forsake, leave."}]}